The file odfdom-java-0.8.7.jar was downloaded from http://odftoolkit.org/.
It was then renamed to odfdom.jar and placed in this folder.

The program was written through The ODF Toolkit Union

ODF (http://opendocument.xml.org/) is the vendor-neutral and 
application-neutral open International Standard for office documents. 
The ODF Toolkit Union is an open source community that develops and hosts 
tools that make it easier to work with ODF documents.

